text: @SarahRotundo1 glad you liked them. Catch up soon.
@Netmums - parents don't always know how to effectively interact with their ey childcare provider #NWBusinessSummit

Now @GillJonesOfsted on the new inspection framework #NWBusinessSummit
Imaginary play is core to understanding how life works. Using emergent language and rehearsing for life #NWBusinessSummit
Natural conversation has the biggest impact on child language acquisition. You don't need to "correct" children #NWBusinessSummit
Help children develop ordered memories by asking specific questions and evaluating #NWBusinessSummit
Young children need routines and repetition to make the world predictable. This is turn helps encoding novel events #NWBusinessSummit
Language is social by definition. You cannot learn it from the TV (or other interactive tech) #NWBusinessSummit
Brand new babies imitate facial expressions - beginning of understanding they're "like us" - this may work for empathy too #NWBusinessSummit

Quality of learning environment (from parents and teachers) is fundamental #NWBusinessSummit
